  "prompt": "When does a Senate motion require 3/5 vote?",
  "response": "In the United States Senate, a motion to invoke cloture requires a three-fifths vote. Cloture is the procedure used to end a filibuster and bring the matter being debated to a vote. Specifically, it requires the approval of 60 senators out of the 100 members of the Senate, except in the case of some specific circumstances like amending Senate rules, which can require a different threshold.",
